# cPanel: Software and Services

## How to Install Perl Modules on cPanel Account

Perl modules are collections of functions that allow you to perform tasks in Perl. You will need to install a Perl module before you can use it inside a Perl program. You can install available perl modules on your account from the cPanel control panel

- Login to your cPanel account
- Under Software/Services click on Perl Modules

```diagram

```

- Perl modules are collections of functions that allow you to perform tasks in Perl. You will need to install a Perl module before you can use it inside a Perl program.
- From the new window you can find the perl module installation location. Its should be  /home/username/perl. Also there is short detail how to use this perl modules in your scripts.

```diagram

```

- Now you can search/install new perl modules under your account. 

```diagram

```


## Install a PHP Pear Package

- Login to cPanel of your account
- Under Software/Services click on PHP PEAR Packages

```diagram

```

- PEAR packages are collections of functions that allow you to perform tasks in PHP. You will need to install a PEAR package before you can use it inside a PHP program.
- Location of Your PHP Extension(s) and Application(s) should be  /home/your_username/php
- Click on Show Available PHP Extensions

```diagram

```

- It will list all available php extensions. Click on install to install extensions.

